import{_ as e,c as t,o as a,a3 as s}from"./chunks/framework.BFHIN2GX.js";const y=JSON.parse('{"title":"Deal With Notimess","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"blog/deal-with-notimess.md","filePath":"blog/deal-with-notimess.md","lastUpdated":1710683667000}'),i={name:"blog/deal-with-notimess.md"},o=s('<h1 id="deal-with-notimess" tabindex="-1">Deal With Notimess <a class="header-anchor" href="#deal-with-notimess" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;Deal With Notimess&quot;">​</a></h1><p>Notification-message, Notimess, which I named are those messages come as notifications. And I think that it is the most part of the information we get everyday.</p><p><strong>How to deal with it?</strong></p><p>You may ask: &quot;Deal with it? Why should I deal with it? It just as usually as eating or sleeping in our daily life.&quot;</p><p>Well, today, Internet creates massive messages from the world, which may overwhelmingly control our lives. Unconsciously, people are sucked in those disorganized information, and loss their directions in this real world.</p><p>To be honest, that is my pain at this moment, and also a specific chance for me to write this blog.</p><p>In morning, it&#39;s easy to open my eyes and phone, and check updates on x, youtube, github, telegram, discord or other social medias. Gradually, I don&#39;t even know who am I, what I want to do. And when I readed those notimesses, I just feel that my brain is almost a blank, a void return value. And there may left some agitation at most. Why there is agitation? Because I&#39;m angry about there is no more updates for me to entertain.</p><p>The result is that, I just know I must wake up, go for breakfirst, and continue my job at my working position. I&#39;m sinking day in and day out, with no hope and any power to go forward.</p><p>「君たちはどう生きるか」、宮崎さんが言ってた。でも、その言葉は俺にはすごく辛いものです。俺は、どこに行くべきかわからない迷い子です</p><p>Many days passed, I noticed a fact: &quot;The situation seems a little strange, I think it&#39;s time to change it&quot;.</p><p>So, what I found is to make some definitions and rules before getting or receiving any notimesses, here it is:</p><p><strong>Definitions:</strong></p><ol><li>Notimesses are messages, objective existences</li><li>Human are subjective existences</li><li>Messages type 1: The gold that I want to search, find, confirm, driven by my curiosity. (Maybe 1%)</li><li>Messages type 2: The staff that is a little interesting, which I want to collect for after-reading. (Maybe 19%)</li><li>Messages type 3: The rubbish that should not be read more than 1 sec. (Maybe 80%)</li></ol><p><strong>Rules:</strong></p><ol><li>I, as a human, must choose the messages initiatively, which I really want to pay attention to.</li><li>Spend 80%, 19% and 1% of my time in type 1, 2, 3 message.</li><li>Dig out the first and second rules and execute, after I lose myself and bury the rules I made into the grave.</li></ol><p>So, as an experiment, let me have a try to test it.</p><p>That&#39;s all, no results yet, but maybe later.</p>',17),n=[o];function r(l,h,d,m,p,c){return a(),t("div",null,n)}const g=e(i,[["render",r]]);export{y as __pageData,g as default};
